<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuIyNQSVZPVCBMT05HIEVGRkVDVCBNQVRSSVhcbmRmX2NyaXNwciA9IFxuICBnZW5lX2VmZmVjdCAlPiUgXG4gIHBpdm90X2xvbmdlcihjb2xzID0gLURlcE1hcF9JRCwgbmFtZXNfdG8gPSBcXFNZTUJPTFxcLCB2YWx1ZXNfdG8gPSBcXGdlbmVfZWZmZWN0XFwpICU+JSBcbiAgbXV0YXRlKFNZTUJPTCA9IGdzdWIoXFwgLipcXCxcXFxcLFNZTUJPTCkpICU+JSBcbiAgZmlsdGVyKFNZTUJPTCAlaW4lIGFjdGlvbmFibGVfZ2VuZXMpXG5cbmhlYWQoZGZfY3Jpc3ByKVxuYGBgXG5gYGByXG5kaW0oZGZfY3Jpc3ByKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
##PIVOT LONG EFFECT MATRIX
df_crispr = 
  gene_effect %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = -DepMap_ID, names_to = \SYMBOL\, values_to = \gene_effect\) %>% 
  mutate(SYMBOL = gsub(\ .*\,\\,SYMBOL)) %>% 
  filter(SYMBOL %in% actionable_genes)

head(df_crispr)
dim(df_crispr)

Add splice variant annotation to spliceAI output data frame
Since this data has already been filtered for SNPs producing a splice variant with >0.5 confidence, as predicted by the NN, we can simply tag all SNPs as TRUE

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuZGZfc3BsaWNlID0gXG4gIGFjdGlvbmFibGVfc3BsaWNlICU+JSBcbiAgbXV0YXRlKHNwbGljZV92YXJpYW50ID0gVFJVRSxcbiAgICAgICAgIHNwbGljZV9nZW5lID0gU1lNQk9MKSAlPiVcbiAgc2VsZWN0KERlcE1hcF9JRCxTWU1CT0wscHJpbWFyeV9kaXNlYXNlLHNwbGljZV92YXJpYW50LHNwbGljZV9nZW5lLE1BWF9QUk9CQUJJTElUWSwgZXhvbl9pbnRyb24pXG5cbmhlYWQoZGZfc3BsaWNlKVxuYGBgXG5gYGByXG5kaW0oZGZfc3BsaWNlKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
df_splice = 
  actionable_splice %>% 
  mutate(splice_variant = TRUE,
         splice_gene = SYMBOL) %>%
  select(DepMap_ID,SYMBOL,primary_disease,splice_variant,splice_gene,MAX_PROBABILITY, exon_intron)

head(df_splice)
dim(df_splice)

Now, let's join the spliceAI output with the CCLE mutation annotation information.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuZGZfc3BsaWNlX2Fubm90ID0gXG4gIGRmX3NwbGljZSAlPiUgXG4gIGxlZnRfam9pbihkZl9tdXRhdGlvbl9tZXRhLCBieSA9IGMoXFxTWU1CT0xcXCwgXFxEZXBNYXBfSURcXCkpICU+JSBcbiAgZGlzdGluY3QoKSAlPiVcbiAgI1N1YnN0aXR1dGUgTkFzIGZyb20gVmFyaWFudF9UeXBlIHdpdGggXFxTTlBcXFxuICBtdXRhdGUoVmFyaWFudF9UeXBlID0gaWZlbHNlKGlzLm5hKFZhcmlhbnRfVHlwZSksIFxcU05QXFwsIFZhcmlhbnRfVHlwZSkpICU+JSBcbiAgc2VsZWN0KC1jKFxccHJpbWFyeV9kaXNlYXNlLnlcXCxcXGlzRGVsZXRlcmlvdXNcXCkpICU+JSBcbiAgcmVuYW1lKFxccHJpbWFyeV9kaXNlYXNlXFwgPSBcXHByaW1hcnlfZGlzZWFzZS54XFwpXG4gIFxuXG5kaW0oZGZfc3BsaWNlX2Fubm90KVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
df_splice_annot = 
  df_splice %>% 
  left_join(df_mutation_meta, by = c(\SYMBOL\, \DepMap_ID\)) %>% 
  distinct() %>%
  #Substitute NAs from Variant_Type with \SNP\
  mutate(Variant_Type = ifelse(is.na(Variant_Type), \SNP\, Variant_Type)) %>% 
  select(-c(\primary_disease.y\,\isDeleterious\)) %>% 
  rename(\primary_disease\ = \primary_disease.x\)
  

dim(df_splice_annot)

<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuZGZfbXV0YXRpb25fZGVsZXQgPSBcbiAgZGZfbXV0YXRpb25fbWV0YSAlPiUgXG4gIG11dGF0ZShpc0RlbCA9IGlmZWxzZShWYXJpYW50X1R5cGUgPT0gXFxTTlBcXCwgRkFMU0UsIFRSVUUpKSAlPiUgXG4gIHNlbGVjdCgtaXNEZWxldGVyaW91cylcblxuZGltKGRmX211dGF0aW9uX2RlbGV0KVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

df_mutation_delet = 
  df_mutation_meta %>% 
  mutate(isDel = ifelse(Variant_Type == \SNP\, FALSE, TRUE)) %>% 
  select(-isDeleterious)

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->



Let's process the mutation metadata in order to tag each gene in each cell line if at least one of the variants in that gene is deleterious.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuZGZfbXV0YXRpb25fZGVsZXRfdGFnID1cbiAgZGZfbXV0YXRpb25fZGVsZXQgJT4lIFxuICBncm91cF9ieShEZXBNYXBfSUQsIFNZTUJPTCkgJT4lIFxuICBzdW1tYXJpc2UoZ2VuZV9kZWxldGVyaW91cyA9IGlmZWxzZShzdW0oaXNEZWwpID4gMCxUUlVFLEZBTFNFKSkgJT4lIFxuICB1bmdyb3VwKClcbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
df_mutation_delet_tag =
  df_mutation_delet %>% 
  group_by(DepMap_ID, SYMBOL) %>% 
  summarise(gene_deleterious = ifelse(sum(isDel) > 0,TRUE,FALSE)) %>% 
  ungroup()

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-output-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYHN1bW1hcmlzZSgpYCBoYXMgZ3JvdXBlZCBvdXRwdXQgYnkgJ0RlcE1hcF9JRCcuIFlvdSBjYW4gb3ZlcnJpZGUgdXNpbmcgdGhlIGAuZ3JvdXBzYCBhcmd1bWVudC5cbiJ9 -->

summarise() has grouped output by DepMap_ID. You can override using the .groups argument.

df_crispr_splice_annot = 
  df_splice_annot %>% 
  full_join(df_crispr, by = c(\DepMap_ID\, \SYMBOL\)) %>% 
  # Cell lines without mutations in the MSK IMPACT genes are annotated as FALSE 
  # in both of the splice_variant and gene_deleterious columns
  mutate(splice_variant = ifelse(is.na(splice_variant),FALSE,splice_variant)) %>% 
  mutate(gene_deleterious = ifelse(is.na(gene_deleterious),FALSE, gene_deleterious)) %>%
  # Filter out cell lines without CRISPR knockdown effect data
  filter(!is.na(gene_effect)) 

head(df_crispr_splice_annot)

#df_crispr_splice_annot %>% 
 # filter(is.na(primary_disease))

#Add disease information for the SNPs coming from gene effect dataframe 
df_crispr_splice_annot = 
  df_crispr_splice_annot %>% 
  left_join(disease_ccle, by = \DepMap_ID\) %>% 
  select(-primary_disease.x) %>% 
  rename(\primary_disease\ = \primary_disease.y\) %>% 
  mutate(variant = case_when(
    splice_variant == TRUE ~ \Var\, 
    splice_variant == FALSE ~ \WT\
  ))

```r
```r
df_crispr_splice_annot %>% 
  group_by(SYMBOL) %>% 
  mutate(sum_splice_variants = sum(splice_variant)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(sum_splice_variants >= 10) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y = gene_effect, x = variant, color = variant)) + 
  geom_quasirandom(method = \pseudorandom\,alpha = 0.5, size = 0.5) + 
  theme_bw() +
  facet_wrap(\SYMBOL\) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(\red\,\black\)) +
  xlab(\\) +
  ylab(\CRISPR gene effect (sd from median)\) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        legend.position = \bottom\) + 
  stat_compare_means(label = \p.format\, label.y = 4.5, label.x = 1)

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

df_crispr_splice_annot %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y = gene_effect, x = variant, color = variant)) + 
  geom_quasirandom(method = "pseudorandom",alpha = 0.5, size = 0.5) + 
  theme_bw() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("red","black")) +
  xlab("") +
  ylab("CRISPR gene effect (sd from median)") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        legend.position = "bottom") + 
  stat_compare_means(label = "p.format", label.y = 4.5, label.x = 1)

df_crispr_splice_annot_bf = 
  df_crispr_splice_annot %>% 
  select(gene_effect, variant)


bf <- bf.test(gene_effect ~ variant, data = df_crispr_splice_annot)
